# gg-singlecell

Plotnine-based plotting utilities for single-cell and genomics analyses.

## Install

```bash
pip install -e .
```

## Quick start

```python
import pandas as pd
from gg_singlecell import plot_reduced_dim

# DataFrame with embeddings
df = pd.DataFrame({"umap_1": [0,1,2], "umap_2": [0.1,0.2,0.3], "cluster": ["A","B","A"]})
p = plot_reduced_dim(df, x="umap_1", y="umap_2", color="cluster")
print(p)
```

## BiocPy SingleCellExperiment

```python
from gg_singlecell import build_plot_df_from_sce, plot_reduced_dim_sce
plot_df = build_plot_df_from_sce(sce, dim_name="UMAP", prefix="umap")
p = plot_reduced_dim_sce(sce, dim_name="UMAP", color="cluster")
```

## SummarizedExperiment
SummarizedExperiment does not store reduced dimensions. Use PCA to derive scores and plot:

```python
from gg_singlecell import build_plot_df_from_se_and_pca, plot_pca_from_se
plot_df = build_plot_df_from_se_and_pca(se, pca_res, n_comps=2, prefix="pca")
p = plot_pca_from_se(se, pca_res, color="condition")
```

## Suggested plots to add
- Gene expression overlay on embeddings
- Violin plots of expression (Seurat-like)
- Marker gene dot-plot (genes × clusters)
- Volcano plots for DE results
- Heatmaps from long-form data or matrices
- QC scatter/histograms and cluster composition barplots

Contributions welcome!

## New APIs

### Expression violin
```python
from gg_singlecell import expression_violin
# DataFrame API
p = expression_violin(df, value="expr", group="cluster", log1p=True)

# SCE/SE convenience
# expression_violin(sce, "MS4A1", group_col="cluster", assay="logcounts")
```

### Volcano plot
```python
from gg_singlecell import volcano_plot
p = volcano_plot(de_df, log2fc="log2FC", padj="FDR", fdr_thresh=0.05, lfc_thresh=1.0)
```

### Heatmap
```python
from gg_singlecell import heatmap_from_matrix
p = heatmap_from_matrix(matrix, row_names=genes, col_names=clusters, zscore_rows=True)
```

### Marker dot-plot
```python
from gg_singlecell import marker_dotplot_from_matrix
p = marker_dotplot_from_matrix(expr_matrix, groups=cluster_series, genes=["CD3D","MS4A1"])
```

### Ridge density
```python
from gg_singlecell import ridge_density
p = ridge_density(df, value="expr", group="cluster", bandwidth=None)
```

### QC plots
```python
from gg_singlecell import qc_scatter, qc_histogram, cluster_composition_barplot
p = qc_scatter(df, x="n_counts", y="n_genes", color="mito_frac")
p = qc_histogram(df, value="mito_frac")
p = cluster_composition_barplot(df, cluster_col="cluster", group_col="condition", normalize=True)
```

## Run tests
```bash
python -m pytest -q
```
